		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">Strategy for fighting casting mobs<br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: Strategy for fighting casting mobs";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sat, Oct 14th 7:11 PM2000 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=10&mid=97156508625900&post=1"><a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=10&mid=97156508625900&post=1&replyto=97156508625900"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=97156508625900></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Is there a workable strategy for fighting casting mobs with a ranger? I have had many blue casters wipe up the ground with me, and I hardly make a dent in them. I was fighting a couple bandits in WK the other day, had one down and was working on the second when suddenly this other one, (I think it was a druid, not sure though.. it was too far away to see clearly) rooted me and started nuking the crap out of me. It was too far away for my spells to do anything, and arrows didn't do much. Fortunately, some little guy come along and got him for me ( I couldn't tell what he was either.. too far away&nbsp;&nbsp;lol).  He killed the druid and ran off before I could thank him. After the root wore off, I limped off to do some healing. I have even had green casters give me one heck of a fight.<br /><br />So far it seems to me, when I fight a mob and it starts casting, I have two choices.. run like crazy or stay and die.<br /><br />So, is there any way to fight a caster? I'm mainly talking soloing. </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >3 Replies</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Oct 16th 3:04 AM2000 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=10&mid=97156508625900&post=1&replyto=9716798614262"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=9716798614262></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=490"><span id=Scholar>mousemaster</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br />20 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=mousemaster&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>YES there is!<br /><br />Ok, here's the drill when fighting casters, rangers or otherwise:<br /><br />ALWAYS get close if you can.&nbsp;&nbsp;In your above example, you didnt have a chance (although me thinks your archery skill is a bit low to have not made much of a dent... :).  In this case, you arrows AND you most powerful nuke in succession...<br /><br />"But they took that ability away" you might say... sort of.  you can no longer cast and fire an arrow, but it CAN be done in reverse.  shoot, cast, wait, repeat, for extra effect.  ALWAYS apply your DoT first (not sure of your level, if u have it).<br /><br />Most times though, you will end up meleeing a caster.  Step one is to have a damage shield up... even if they are iceing you senseless, they attack between casts, so might as well get thta damage in.  Step 2:  apply a DoT if available... and NO other spells.  save your snare for when it runs away, otherwise u want to be swinging the whole time.<br /><br />As for your choice of weapon, get as HIGH of a delay weapon as you can (and yes, as high a damage one as well :).  Since the odds are they will have a damage shield of their own up, you want to make every blow as powerful as possible, while not swinging lightning fast and killing yourself.<br /><br />also, if you know that you're about to face a fire-caster, get that endure fire up.  20 may not sound like much, but it IS.  its saved me more than it should have, but it did.<br /><br />lastly, get sets of armor that are designed to repel your current adversary.  I.E. if you are going to tackle a cold-caster, get a polar bear cloak, etc.  if their spells do less, all the better... casters whos casting is ignorable are easier to kill than pre-snared tanks.<br /><br />hope this helps.. and raise your archery :)</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Wildkat, Xegony<br />Jendar, Tholuxe Paells<br /><br />I post, therefore... I play :)</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >4 Replies</td></tr></table>
